document_data.Powers:
There were several [[magic]]al ropes that were used in the Realms, such as:
* ''[[Rope of climbing|Ropes of climbing]]'', enchanted ropes that could support over a ton of weight and even knot or unknot themselves.{{Cite card/AD&D Trading Cards/1992|54|Dathan of Thunderstone}}{{Cite card/AD&D Trading Cards/1992|560|Jadethread}}
* ''[[Rope of immutable binding|Ropes of immutable binding]]'', enchanted ropes that would constrict around those that attempted to break or escape from being bound by them.<ref>{{Cite dragon/281/Rogues Gallery: Heroes of the Summoning|80}}
* ''[[Rope of mending|Ropes of mending]]'', wondrous ropes that could be easily cut apart into smaller lengths and mended back together with ease.
* ''[[Rope of entanglement|Ropes of entanglement]]'', ropes that could lash forward and bind several creatures.
* ''[[Spider rope]]s'', ropes that could be commanded to grow in length and tie their ends to inanimate objects.<ref>{{Cite dragon/256/Bazaar of the Bizarre: Tools of the Trade|92}}

document_data.Notable Rope Merchants:
* ''[[Aurora's Whole Realms Catalogue (in-universe)|Aurora's Whole Realms Catalogue]]'' sold strong hempen ropes and [[elf|elven]] silk ropes, each priced per {{SI|50|ft}}. The thinnest hemp ropes had {{SI|{{#expr:1/16}}|inch|m}} diameters and sold only for 5 [[cp]] each, whilst the thickest hemp ropes had {{SI|4|inch|c}} diameters and cost 28 [[gp]] each. The thickest silk ropes cost 50 [[gp]]. The catalogue also sold triple-stranded elven silk rope as part of [[rope set]]s.
* The shop known as [[Ropes for All Uses]], which was located in the Zakharan city of [[Huzuz]], sold many different types of ropes, both normal and extraordinary.{{AQ-time}}
* The city of [[Tantras]] was well known for having a number of expert ropemakers. A typical rope shop was owned by one or more masters, with six to eight skilled workers and a handful of apprentices in their employ that all worked to ‘weave’ the ropes by hand.<ref>{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2004)/General Facts on Tantras}}
* In the city of [[Thentia]], the merchant [[Dost Birneir]] sold for low prices rope and other small goods that he had imported from other parts of Faerûn.<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/79/The Everwinking Eye: Inside Thentia|8}}
* In the city of [[Waterdeep]], the vast amount of ropes used by ships were supplied by the [[Most Diligent League of Sail-Makers and Cordwainers]], though they struggled to keep up with demand. Alternatively, the [[Master Mariners' Guild]] kept emergency stocks of rope that its members could purchase at bargain rates.
